// Function to remove duplicates from an array and sort it
function removeDuplicatesAndSort(arr) {
    // Remove duplicates
    let uniqueArr = [...new Set(arr)];

    // Sort the array in ascending order
    uniqueArr.sort((a, b) => a - b);

    // Return the sorted array with no duplicates
    return uniqueArr;
}
```

This function first removes duplicates using the `Set` object, then sorts the array in ascending order using the `sort()` method. The `sort()` method sorts the elements of an array in place and returns the array. The default sort order is built upon converting the elements into strings, then comparing their sequences of UTF-16 code unit values. To sort numbers in ascending order, you need to pass a comparison function that takes two arguments and returns a negative, zero, or positive value, depending on the arguments. In this case, `(a, b) => a - b` is used to sort the numbers in ascending order.

